This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with the task of headline generation, which is a subfield of NLP. Additionally, the paper utilizes techniques of reinforcement learning (RL), which is a popular approach in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves attention mechanisms and predictor models, which are commonly used in deep learning and neural network architectures (cs.LG). The task of headline generation also involves information retrieval and text summarization, which are subfields of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the task of generating attractive headlines, which involves predicting the popularity of the generated headlines, a task that can be viewed as a form of predictive modeling (cs.NE).
